<!DOCTYPE html>

html lang="en"
  head
    meta charset="utf-8"
    title - TK
    meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1"
    link rel="stylesheet" href="${data.path_to_asset('scss', 'stylesheets/index.css')}"
    $!{data.render_template('_social-meta', data)}
  body
    $!{data.helpers.nav()}

    article
      p - Search here, and see what comes up!

      #app data-tsv-path="${data.path_to_asset('digest', 'data/clinton-trump-token-counts-truncated.tsv')}"
        .search
          input autofocus name="q" id="q" autocomplete="off" type="text" placeholder="Type a word…"
          .autocomplete.input-empty
          .result
            <!-- only the last element will be visible -->
            .loading - Loading…
            label.empty for="q" - Please search for a word
            <!-- .hit - <svg>..... -->

      h2 - What's this?

      p - Here's how we made this tool:

      ol
        li - We downloaded all follower information for Trump and Clinton.
        li - We broke down each Twitter bio into words.
        li - For each word, we counted how many Twitter bios contained that word.
        li - We omitted all words that fewer than 100 Trump and/or Clinton followers used in their bios.

    $!{data.helpers.footer()}
